  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Komal Krishan Arora & Ors. versus Sandeep Kumar & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_9_1085_1109','2025INSC1123'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KOMAL KRISHAN ARORA & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SANDEEP KUMAR & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1085</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1123</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008872025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.K. MAHESHWARI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the directions issued by the High Court that the interim custody of the minor son aged five years be handed over to the father from the custody of the maternal grandfather warrants interference. Headnotes&dagger; Custody &ndash; Child custody &ndash; &ndash; Strained marital relationship of the parents &ndash; Mother left India for UK with both the children-minor daughter and son, allegedly without the father&rsquo;s knowledge or consent &ndash; Father initiated proceedings in UK High Court seeking return of the children &ndash; UK Court<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 4052/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_9_1085_1109','2025INSC1123','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'>